WEBVTT

00:01.100 --> 00:02.890
You and me, Saturday night.

00:02.930 --> 00:04.320
I am taking you out.

00:04.370 --> 00:05.320
Are you sure?

00:05.370 --> 00:06.850
[Will]
Yep, absolutely.

00:06.890 --> 00:08.980
You don't have plans
with the wife and kid?

00:09.030 --> 00:10.510
Ha-ha.
Fiona's not my wife.

00:10.550 --> 00:11.810
Marcus is not my kid.

00:11.850 --> 00:13.200
Okay, well, you have to admit,

00:13.250 --> 00:14.940
your relationship with them
is pretty odd.

00:14.990 --> 00:16.730
Sometimes odd,
sometimes quite normal.

00:16.770 --> 00:17.950
She accosted my kid

00:17.990 --> 00:20.080
and basically attacked me
the other night.

00:20.120 --> 00:21.820
Okay, well,
that would go in the odd bin.

00:21.860 --> 00:24.170
- You know, Will--
- You and me, Saturday night.

00:24.210 --> 00:25.610
No distractions. Okay?

00:25.650 --> 00:28.000
- Okay.
- No distractions.

00:28.040 --> 00:29.000
Okay.

00:29.050 --> 00:32.010
[quirky music]

00:32.050 --> 00:33.090
♪

00:33.140 --> 00:36.960
Oh, man.

00:37.010 --> 00:39.450
My life used to be so simple.

00:39.490 --> 00:41.750
[knock at door]

00:41.800 --> 00:43.100
I mean, come on.

00:43.150 --> 00:44.280
Story?

00:44.320 --> 00:46.240
This is Shell Silverstein.

00:46.280 --> 00:49.150
He's an emotional support turtle
I've procured for Marcus

00:49.200 --> 00:51.210
to help him get over
his breakup with Shea.

00:51.240 --> 00:52.850
And before you make

00:52.890 --> 00:54.850
some ridiculous,
immature comment,

00:54.900 --> 00:57.510
I would like to remind you
that this horrific mess

00:57.550 --> 00:58.990
is largely your fault.

00:59.030 --> 01:00.510
Just because I bring Clay along
on a date

01:00.550 --> 01:01.770
does not mean that
that the whole--

01:01.820 --> 01:03.860
[footsteps]

01:03.910 --> 01:05.700
Whoa, Nellie.

01:08.040 --> 01:11.130
Darling, why don't you have
a snuggle off Mr. Shell.

01:11.170 --> 01:12.390
I've tuned our ukes.

01:12.440 --> 01:15.130
Now, what do you want to
start with?

01:15.180 --> 01:17.570
We Shall Overcome
or Amazing Grace?

01:17.620 --> 01:19.800
I can't just sit by
and watch this happen.

01:19.830 --> 01:21.620
Marcus, you need to go
back to school,

01:21.660 --> 01:23.320
you need to hold
your head up high,

01:23.360 --> 01:25.750
and you need to show Shea
and the rest of the world

01:25.800 --> 01:28.800
that you're super fine
without her.

01:28.840 --> 01:31.240
Maybe it is time for me
to face society again.

01:31.280 --> 01:34.070
I think we should do five
or six verses of Amazing Grace

01:34.110 --> 01:36.370
and then see where
that leaves us.

01:36.420 --> 01:39.510
♪ Amazing Grace

01:39.550 --> 01:40.680
[groans]

01:40.730 --> 01:42.300
I can see why you wanted to
run away.

01:42.340 --> 01:43.950
[Fiona and Marcus]
♪ How sweet the sound

01:43.990 --> 01:45.600
This is torture
for that guy.

01:45.640 --> 01:47.120
[man]
Here we go.

01:47.170 --> 01:50.340
[Brett Dennen's Comeback Kid
[That's My Dog]]

01:50.390 --> 01:53.040
♪ Well, maybe
it's the common curse ♪

01:53.090 --> 01:56.270
♪ Maybe things get bad
before they get worse ♪

01:56.310 --> 01:58.130
♪ I don't want
to become someone ♪

01:58.180 --> 02:02.050
♪ Who can't live up
to what I already done, don't ♪

02:02.090 --> 02:03.570
♪ Here comes a comeback

02:03.620 --> 02:06.180
♪ The kid is back,
is back on track ♪

02:06.230 --> 02:09.190
♪ And there goes my hero

02:09.230 --> 02:13.060
♪ He's the underdog,
he's coming out on top, and ♪

02:13.110 --> 02:15.330
[cheers and applause]

02:16.330 --> 02:19.720
[quirky music]

02:19.760 --> 02:22.810
Psss, okay,
I did not anticipate this.

02:22.850 --> 02:24.510
I told you
this was too soon.

02:24.550 --> 02:27.510
[kids chatting]

02:27.550 --> 02:30.250
If this turns out badly, Will,
I blame you.

02:30.300 --> 02:32.910
- Oh, there we are.
- Hold Shell Silverstein.

02:32.950 --> 02:34.260
Good luck, darling.

02:34.300 --> 02:41.220
♪

02:41.260 --> 02:43.830
Hey, where have you been
the past few days?

02:43.880 --> 02:47.280
You know, just
hanging and chilling.

02:49.450 --> 02:51.800
I've been performing healing
rituals in the love bubble

02:51.840 --> 02:54.150
with my mom, and if I'm to be
totally honest with you,

02:54.190 --> 02:56.890
we burned a lot of your stuff
in effigy.

02:56.930 --> 02:58.760
You're so weird, Marcus.

02:58.800 --> 02:59.930
[chuckles]

02:59.980 --> 03:02.070
Hey, so I got our tix
for the dance.

03:02.110 --> 03:03.720
- Cool.
- Hey, Marv.

03:03.760 --> 03:06.720
[quirky music]

03:06.770 --> 03:08.030
♪

03:08.070 --> 03:09.030
[sighs]

03:09.070 --> 03:14.030
♪

03:14.080 --> 03:15.040
Hey, buddy.

03:15.080 --> 03:16.120
Listen.

03:16.170 --> 03:17.910
Granted that
this Love In The Air thing

03:17.950 --> 03:19.390
is a bit of a dark wrinkle,

03:19.430 --> 03:21.300
I still think it was a good idea
that you came to school.

03:21.350 --> 03:24.740
Will, my future has become
crystal clear to me now.

03:24.790 --> 03:25.800
Home schooling.

03:25.830 --> 03:27.790
Enough of this.
New plan, all right?

03:27.830 --> 03:29.490
No longer are we going
into school

03:29.530 --> 03:30.960
just hoping to blend in.

03:31.010 --> 03:32.530
We are gonna go full makeover,

03:32.580 --> 03:33.750
you're gonna go
to that dance,

03:33.790 --> 03:35.100
and you're gonna get
a new girl.

03:35.140 --> 03:37.670
I think you may be
confusing me for you, Will.

03:37.710 --> 03:39.060
You don't know this yet,
Marcus,

03:39.100 --> 03:40.890
but your stock
has gone way up.

03:40.930 --> 03:43.330
You were just dating
the cutest girl in school.

03:43.370 --> 03:44.630
Every girl knows it.

03:44.680 --> 03:46.120
So you are
going to the dance,

03:46.150 --> 03:47.850
you are going to bag
a new babe,

03:47.900 --> 03:50.040
and I am so excited
about it

03:50.070 --> 03:52.030
that I'm gonna come along
with you as your wingman.

03:52.070 --> 03:53.860
Let's go get some tickets.

03:53.900 --> 03:55.080
How did it go?

03:55.120 --> 03:56.560
It went great.

03:56.600 --> 03:58.300
I'm gonna give Marcus
a nice little makeover,

03:58.340 --> 03:59.690
I'm gonna take him
to the dance,

03:59.730 --> 04:01.520
and I'm gonna help him bag
a new babe.

04:01.560 --> 04:02.950
- What?
- Now give me the keys.

04:03.000 --> 04:04.300
- I'm driving home.
- What do you mean? I--no.

04:04.350 --> 04:05.520
You almost got in
five accidents on the way--

04:05.570 --> 04:07.100
- Well, I was very emotional.
- Exactly.

04:07.130 --> 04:08.440
- So this is why I should drive.
- No, you're not driving.

04:08.480 --> 04:09.440
- Give me the keys.
- No, I--

04:09.480 --> 04:10.440
You are in no place--

04:10.480 --> 04:11.790
- Give me--
- Just let go.

04:11.830 --> 04:13.010
- I'm gonna bite your finger.
[Fiona shouts]

04:13.050 --> 04:14.360
Hey!

04:14.400 --> 04:16.530
So, what's going on here?

04:16.580 --> 04:18.230
Nothing, we're just having
one of our little spats.

04:18.270 --> 04:19.230
- Yeah.
- Hmm.

04:19.280 --> 04:20.850
Just like an old married couple.

04:20.890 --> 04:22.240
- Not old.
- Married?

04:22.280 --> 04:23.630
- Get in the car.
- I'm not gonna get in the car.

04:23.670 --> 04:24.450
- Get in the car.
- I'm not getting in the car.

04:24.500 --> 04:25.580
[Will]
Just get in the car.

04:25.630 --> 04:26.890
You can't make me get
in the car!

04:26.930 --> 04:28.020
Get in the car.
Just give me three minutes.

04:28.070 --> 04:29.110
- And get in the car!
- Let me out.

04:29.150 --> 04:31.020
Five seconds!

04:31.070 --> 04:32.110
What's going on?

04:32.160 --> 04:33.160
She gonna be okay in there?

04:33.200 --> 04:34.250
Yeah, she's fine.

04:34.290 --> 04:35.940
Just crack a window!
Crack a window.

04:35.990 --> 04:36.940
- [whining]
- She's fine.

04:36.990 --> 04:38.900
[groans]

04:38.950 --> 04:40.990
Well, I can see
you're a little busy...

04:41.040 --> 04:42.220
- No, no.
- At the moment.

04:42.250 --> 04:44.210
So, I'll just see you
on Saturday.

04:44.260 --> 04:45.820
Yeah, I'll s--

04:45.870 --> 04:47.170
Saturday.

04:47.220 --> 04:49.100
[Liz]
Is there a problem?

04:49.130 --> 04:50.170
- There is, isn't there?
- No.

04:50.220 --> 04:51.740
And I'm willing to bet

04:51.790 --> 04:53.230
that it is Marcus
and Fiona related.

04:53.270 --> 04:54.800
No, there's no problem.

04:54.830 --> 04:56.180
Just shh.

04:56.220 --> 04:58.100
It's not a problem at all.
Here's the deal.

04:58.140 --> 05:00.660
I was thinking,
instead of going out to dinner,

05:00.710 --> 05:04.750
what if we went to
the Love is in the Air dance...

05:04.800 --> 05:05.760
[laughs]
What?

05:05.800 --> 05:07.020
On Saturday?

05:07.060 --> 05:09.060
You want to take me
to a middle school dance?

05:09.110 --> 05:10.800
Yeah, well, you know,
you told me you never had

05:10.850 --> 05:12.110
a prom experience,

05:12.150 --> 05:13.630
so let's pretend
we're chaperones,

05:13.680 --> 05:15.680
but instead, just have, like,
an awesome time together.

05:15.720 --> 05:17.330
You can have the prom experience
you never had.

05:17.380 --> 05:20.770
I'm gonna pick you up at 7:00
in a limo at your house,

05:20.810 --> 05:22.030
and we're going, okay?

05:22.080 --> 05:23.030
- Are you sure?
- Yeah.

05:23.080 --> 05:24.250
Just you and me, right?

05:24.300 --> 05:25.560
- It's the gonna be the--
- [chuckles]

05:25.600 --> 05:29.340
It's gonna be the best
prom experience ever.

05:29.390 --> 05:30.350
[chuckles]

05:30.390 --> 05:32.650
Okay.

05:32.700 --> 05:33.650
[sighs]

05:33.700 --> 05:35.870
You bastard.

05:35.920 --> 05:38.090
We barely had enough oxygen
to breathe in there...

05:38.140 --> 05:39.180
- Cracked window right there.
- Shell and I.

05:39.220 --> 05:40.180
Ridiculous statement.

05:40.230 --> 05:41.450
We have decided

05:41.490 --> 05:43.230
that we are going to be
chaperones,

05:43.270 --> 05:44.620
Shell and I, for this dance.

05:44.660 --> 05:45.710
You are not
going to the dance.

05:45.750 --> 05:46.970
Oh, yes, I am.

05:47.010 --> 05:48.320
Marcus has to have
somebody there for him.

05:48.360 --> 05:50.630
Soon as I find out
if it is all right to bring

05:50.670 --> 05:53.370
a license-pending
therapeutic turtle.

05:53.410 --> 05:55.240
Ridiculous.

05:56.850 --> 05:58.940
♪ I'm bringing
all my hat tricks ♪

05:58.980 --> 06:00.810
♪ I'm using sleight of hand

06:00.850 --> 06:03.250
♪ Bounce back like I'm elastic

06:03.290 --> 06:04.900
♪ I feel good,
I'm feeling grand ♪

06:04.950 --> 06:07.300
♪ I pull out
from out my sleeve now ♪

06:07.340 --> 06:09.600
♪ Flowers and handkerchiefs

06:09.650 --> 06:11.600
♪ I win crowds
and take a bow now ♪

06:11.650 --> 06:13.650
♪ I give you just what
you need ♪

06:13.690 --> 06:15.910
♪ In the spotlight,
in the spotlight ♪

06:15.960 --> 06:17.650
♪ In the spotlight,
in the spotlight ♪

06:17.700 --> 06:19.920
♪ I make the stars shine,
make the stars shine ♪

06:19.960 --> 06:22.530
♪ I make the stars shine

06:22.570 --> 06:23.570
♪ Hey

06:23.620 --> 06:25.750
♪ I got the magic

06:25.790 --> 06:28.270
♪ Yeah, I'm the ace

06:28.320 --> 06:30.540
♪ In the pack

06:30.580 --> 06:32.450
♪ I said hey

06:32.500 --> 06:34.770
♪ I bring the magic

06:34.800 --> 06:36.670
♪ 'Cause we all

06:36.720 --> 06:41.070
♪ Need some of that,
need some of that, yeah ♪

06:41.110 --> 06:42.290
Is she walking towards me?

06:42.330 --> 06:43.590
♪

06:43.640 --> 06:44.590
[record scratches]

06:44.640 --> 06:45.770
Is that your baby?

06:45.810 --> 06:48.600
She is so adorable.

06:48.640 --> 06:50.250
- Thank you.
- I am practically

06:50.300 --> 06:52.390
this little miracle's uncle.

06:52.430 --> 06:54.210
Oh, wait, you're Marcus,
right?

06:54.260 --> 06:55.610
You and Shea are, like,
together?

06:55.650 --> 06:57.690
We were, but then
she dumped me for a--

06:57.740 --> 06:59.610
Marcus has moved on
from Shea.

06:59.650 --> 07:01.520
Oh, that's too bad.

07:01.570 --> 07:03.740
Actually, technically,
he's avail

07:03.790 --> 07:05.480
for the dance
on Saturday night, right, bud?

07:05.530 --> 07:06.620
Oh, cool.

07:06.660 --> 07:08.270
Well, you know,
I'm available, too.

07:08.310 --> 07:09.490
You hear that, buddy?

07:09.530 --> 07:10.750
She's available too.

07:10.790 --> 07:13.100
Marcus?

07:13.140 --> 07:14.620
What's going on?

07:14.670 --> 07:16.060
Snap out of it.

07:16.100 --> 07:17.320
[Andy]
Snap out of it.

07:17.370 --> 07:18.850
Excuse us for one sec.

07:18.890 --> 07:21.190
Dude, are you going into
a fugue state?

07:21.240 --> 07:22.200
I don't know.

07:22.240 --> 07:23.760
Part of going into
a fugue state

07:23.810 --> 07:25.550
is not knowing
when you're going into one.

07:25.590 --> 07:26.640
Listen to me.

07:26.680 --> 07:28.680
Open up
your entire nervous system

07:28.730 --> 07:30.040
and just repeat
whatever words

07:30.070 --> 07:31.510
you hear me saying, okay?

07:31.550 --> 07:32.550
Okay.

07:35.510 --> 07:37.690
- I'd be honored...
- I'd be honored...

07:37.730 --> 07:40.610
If you'd go to the Love is
in the Air dance with me.

07:40.650 --> 07:42.520
If you'd go to the...

07:42.570 --> 07:44.100
♪

07:44.130 --> 07:45.700
The...

07:45.740 --> 07:49.270
♪

07:49.310 --> 07:50.270
I'm sorry.

07:50.310 --> 07:51.700
You're a really nice girl,

07:51.750 --> 07:55.140
but I'd be doing you wrong
by taking you to this dance.

07:55.190 --> 07:56.710
That's way off book.
Way off book.

07:56.750 --> 07:58.970
My heart is already spoken for.

07:59.020 --> 08:01.150
It is owned by
Shea Garcia-Miller,

08:01.190 --> 08:03.500
and I have to go
to this dance alone

08:03.540 --> 08:04.720
to win back my love.

08:04.760 --> 08:05.890
Jerk.

08:05.940 --> 08:08.500
And your baby isn't even
that cute.

08:08.550 --> 08:09.550
[scoffs]

08:09.590 --> 08:11.640
Wha--huh?

08:11.680 --> 08:14.030
Well, you smell like poo.

08:14.070 --> 08:15.860
- That's the baby.
- That is the baby.

08:15.900 --> 08:19.340
Okay, where's a changing table
in this place?

08:23.000 --> 08:25.000
Well, you've really bungled
this one, haven't you?

08:25.040 --> 08:26.910
Because of you,
my little boy

08:26.960 --> 08:29.390
has to go to this dance
ostensibly alone.

08:29.440 --> 08:30.740
Okay, I've bungled nothing.

08:30.790 --> 08:32.180
I was about to
get him a date,

08:32.220 --> 08:34.700
and he went fugue on me,
and then he went rogue.

08:34.750 --> 08:36.570
Listen to me,
and listen very carefully.

08:36.620 --> 08:39.580
Tonight I am off duty, okay?

08:39.620 --> 08:41.230
I need to salvage
my relationship with Liz.

08:41.280 --> 08:44.770
So bring Marcus's cloak,
your turtles, your ukes--

08:44.800 --> 08:46.580
whatever it is you need.

08:46.630 --> 08:48.590
Tonight,
you are on Marcus duty.

08:48.630 --> 08:50.980
Thank you very much
and good day.

08:51.020 --> 08:52.460
Oh, my God, Will.

08:52.500 --> 08:54.160
I just looked out
the window.

08:54.200 --> 08:56.860
You got me a limo
to make a grand entrance

08:56.900 --> 08:59.340
leading up to my grand gesture
to win back Shea!

08:59.380 --> 09:00.900
I did not.

09:00.950 --> 09:02.820
Wait, he wants to
win back Shea?

09:02.860 --> 09:03.910
Yeah, in my limo.
Come on!

09:03.950 --> 09:05.860
Oh.

09:05.910 --> 09:07.560
Hey, oh, Marcus.

09:07.610 --> 09:08.740
Hey, listen, buddy.

09:08.780 --> 09:10.870
There...hey, hey,
whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

09:10.910 --> 09:11.830
[chuckles]

09:11.870 --> 09:13.870
Uh...how do I explain this?

09:13.920 --> 09:15.610
[Fiona]
Hold on, darling.
Listen.

09:15.660 --> 09:18.050
You are a wonderful person,

09:18.100 --> 09:21.670
and I'm just not sure
that Shea has the maturity

09:21.710 --> 09:23.750
to appreciate that just yet.

09:23.800 --> 09:25.880
I want to take that chance.

09:25.930 --> 09:29.150
I need to take that chance.

09:29.190 --> 09:31.590
Thank you so much
for doing this for me, Will.

09:31.630 --> 09:35.330
It means the world to me.

09:35.370 --> 09:36.720
[sobs]

09:36.770 --> 09:39.330
Oh!
I've never been in a limo.

09:39.380 --> 09:40.770
[squeals]
Oh, my God!

09:40.810 --> 09:42.900
There's chocolate-covered
strawberries and champagne.

09:42.950 --> 09:45.510
I knew I was right to take
some of this fabric.

09:45.560 --> 09:47.120
Let's roll.

09:47.170 --> 09:49.950
♪

09:50.000 --> 09:51.000
Liz is gonna kill me.

09:54.130 --> 09:56.480
[pop rock music playing]

09:56.520 --> 09:59.790
♪

09:59.830 --> 10:00.790
♪ Tonight

10:00.830 --> 10:03.010
There she is.

10:03.050 --> 10:04.790
There's my love.

10:04.840 --> 10:07.360
♪

10:07.410 --> 10:08.460
Oh, hang on, look.

10:08.490 --> 10:10.100
It's all--
it's all falling down.

10:10.150 --> 10:11.580
Look, droopy.
Hold on.

10:11.630 --> 10:13.760
Here, you want to be careful
that that doesn't stick her

10:13.800 --> 10:15.670
if she gets all snuggly
or anything.

10:15.720 --> 10:17.150
[clears throat]
Hi.

10:17.200 --> 10:18.680
- Hey.
- Oh.

10:18.720 --> 10:21.640
Great, so you brought Fiona to
the dance instead of me?

10:21.680 --> 10:23.120
- No, no, no, no, no, no, no.
- I was just fixing his thing.

10:23.160 --> 10:25.470
I don't really need to hear
anything from you right now.

10:25.510 --> 10:26.730
Whoa.
Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa.

10:26.770 --> 10:28.290
I'm--I'm gonna go inside
and chaperone.

10:28.340 --> 10:29.860
Liz, I can explain.
I can explain.

10:29.910 --> 10:31.380
[sighs]
You know, in the beginning,

10:31.430 --> 10:33.740
I sensed that
whatever was going on

10:33.780 --> 10:36.170
between you and Marcus
and Fiona was weird,

10:36.220 --> 10:38.780
but you insisted that it wasn't,
so I trusted you.

10:38.830 --> 10:40.740
Believe me,
it is not what it looks like.

10:40.790 --> 10:43.530
It looks like
you had a choice to make.

10:43.570 --> 10:45.400
Me or Marcus and Fiona.

10:45.440 --> 10:46.920
And once again,
you chose them.

10:46.970 --> 10:48.360
Marcus is devastated.

10:48.400 --> 10:50.140
Your son, Clay, stole Shea.

10:50.190 --> 10:52.750
Oh, my gosh,
they're kids, Will.

10:52.800 --> 10:54.890
They break up,
and then they get back together,

10:54.930 --> 10:56.280
and then they break up again.

10:56.320 --> 10:57.500
It's what they do.

10:57.540 --> 11:00.940
Look, I care about Marcus,
okay?

11:00.980 --> 11:01.980
And I'm not ashamed to say it.

11:02.030 --> 11:05.300
Yeah, well, Will,
I have a son, too.

11:05.330 --> 11:07.770
