13:24.910 --> 13:26.040
I liked her a lot, Fiona.

13:26.080 --> 13:27.040
So, thank you.

13:27.080 --> 13:28.390
Thank you so much.

13:28.430 --> 13:30.610
I hope you're bloody well
not trying to blame me.

13:30.650 --> 13:32.300
How--how could I not?

13:32.350 --> 13:34.830
She literally said
you were the reason.

13:37.180 --> 13:38.270
Sorry.
I mean,

13:38.310 --> 13:39.790
I'm a bit upset right now,

13:39.840 --> 13:41.630
and I think you're upset,
so perhaps the best thing

13:41.660 --> 13:42.880
that we could do is
some Ujjayi yoga breathing.

13:42.930 --> 13:44.890
Ujjayi?
No-jayi!

13:44.930 --> 13:46.620
No memory hole.
No tempeh.

13:46.670 --> 13:48.890
No herbal tea.
Do you understand something?

13:48.930 --> 13:50.060
I had a great life, Fiona.

13:50.110 --> 13:51.320
I had a wonderful life.

13:51.370 --> 13:54.150
I loved it.
I woke up at noon every day.

13:54.200 --> 13:55.890
My best part of my day
was figuring out

13:55.940 --> 13:57.940
which of the many girls
at my disposal

13:57.980 --> 14:00.420
that I got to bring home
for the night.

14:00.460 --> 14:01.550
And then you come along,

14:01.600 --> 14:03.910
and you just ruin everything.

14:03.950 --> 14:06.160
It's like,
I can't even man a grill

14:06.210 --> 14:07.170
when I want to
man a grill.

14:07.210 --> 14:09.120
I'm building tree houses.

14:09.170 --> 14:12.080
Your insane, penguin-obsessed
ex-husband comes over,

14:12.130 --> 14:16.480
and he's staying in my place
and in my bed--naked.

14:16.520 --> 14:20.480
You take out my crazy
stalker ex-girlfriend to tea,

14:20.530 --> 14:22.570
and then she sues me.

14:22.620 --> 14:25.050
I, like, don't now
have any money.

14:25.100 --> 14:29.060
So just...here's the deal.

14:29.100 --> 14:31.970
You stay on your side of
the dumbwaiter

14:32.020 --> 14:33.630
from now on, get it?

14:33.670 --> 14:36.150
You have ruined my life.

14:36.200 --> 14:39.160
[party music]

14:39.200 --> 14:40.160
♪

14:40.200 --> 14:41.550
Did you ever think
for a second

14:41.590 --> 14:44.030
that maybe you ruined my life?

14:44.070 --> 14:47.160
That Marcus and I were
completely happy

14:47.210 --> 14:51.120
before you showed up and started
feeding him red meat and sugar,

14:51.170 --> 14:56.000
things that I have
never condoned nor ever will.

14:56.040 --> 14:59.960
Or do you think I enjoy the fact
that you,

15:00.000 --> 15:03.090
a man who has accomplished
precisely nothing with his life,

15:03.140 --> 15:06.020
is my son's primary
male role model?

15:06.050 --> 15:08.180
You made him think
you cared about him.

15:08.230 --> 15:11.320
You were just looking out
for yourself, Will.

15:11.360 --> 15:14.360
You took your girlfriend's son
on Marcus's date

15:14.410 --> 15:16.970
because it was what was best
for you.

15:17.020 --> 15:18.110
Oh, yeah, okay.

15:18.150 --> 15:19.930
You want to go back
to your shallow life

15:19.980 --> 15:22.110
of sleeping till noon
and your bagels

15:22.150 --> 15:24.030
and shagging girls who are
15 years too young for you--

15:24.070 --> 15:25.680
Yes! Yes.
I want that.

15:25.720 --> 15:27.160
How many times
do I have to tell you?

15:27.200 --> 15:28.250
- I want that back.
- Okay, good!

15:28.290 --> 15:30.420
Have it back.
Stay away from us.

15:30.470 --> 15:32.340
Stay away from Marcus.
Stay away from me.

15:32.380 --> 15:33.860
Stay out of
our love bubble, okay?

15:33.910 --> 15:35.050
No problem.

